<body>
  <header>
    <h1>Cyber Laws with Real-World Examples</h1>
  </header>

  <div class="container">

    <div class="law-box">
      <div class="law-title">1. Unauthorized Access (Hacking)</div>
      <div class="law-section"><span class="label">Definition:</span> Gaining unauthorized access to computer systems or data.</div>
      <div class="law-section"><span class="label">Example:</span> In 2018, the UIDAI Aadhaar system reportedly suffered a data breach where access to over a billion identities was allegedly sold for ₹500.</div>
      <div class="law-section"><span class="label">Crime Under:</span> IT Act 2000, Section 66; Computer Fraud and Abuse Act (USA)</div>
    </div>

    <div class="law-box">
      <div class="law-title">2. Data Protection & Privacy</div>
      <div class="law-section"><span class="label">Definition:</span> Governs collection, use, and storage of personal data.</div>
      <div class="law-section"><span class="label">Example:</span> Facebook-Cambridge Analytica scandal (2018) — millions of Facebook users’ personal data was harvested without consent for political advertising.</div>
      <div class="law-section"><span class="label">Crime Under:</span> GDPR (EU); IT Act Section 72A (India)</div>
    </div>

    <div class="law-box">
      <div class="law-title">3. Cyberstalking and Online Harassment</div>
      <div class="law-section"><span class="label">Definition:</span> Use of electronic communication to stalk or harass individuals.</div>
      <div class="law-section"><span class="label">Example:</span> In 2017, a Bengaluru techie was arrested for stalking and sending threatening emails to a female colleague.</div>
      <div class="law-section"><span class="label">Crime Under:</span> IPC Section 354D; IT Act Section 66A</div>
    </div>

    <div class="law-box">
      <div class="law-title">4. Cyberterrorism</div>
      <div class="law-section"><span class="label">Definition:</span> Use of digital tools to threaten national security or critical infrastructure.</div>
      <div class="law-section"><span class="label">Example:</span> In 2008, Indian government websites were targeted during tensions with Pakistan, highlighting threats to national cyber infrastructure.</div>
      <div class="law-section"><span class="label">Crime Under:</span> IT Act Section 66F</div>
    </div>

    <div class="law-box">
      <div class="law-title">5. Online Defamation</div>
      <div class="law-section"><span class="label">Definition:</span> Publishing false statements online to harm someone’s reputation.</div>
      <div class="law-section"><span class="label">Example:</span> A Bollywood actress filed a defamation case in 2019 after false rumors about her personal life were spread via Instagram and blogs.</div>
      <div class="law-section"><span class="label">Crime Under:

</span> IPC Sections 499 & 500</div>
    </div>

    <div class="law-box">
      <div class="law-title">6. Identity Theft</div>
      <div class="law-section"><span class="label">Definition:</span> Fraudulently using another person’s identity or credentials online.</div>
      <div class="law-section"><span class="label">Example:</span> In 2021, cybercriminals in India used stolen PAN and Aadhaar details to apply for fraudulent loans from instant loan apps.</div>
      <div class="law-section"><span class="label">Crime Under:</span> IT Act Section 66C</div>
    </div>

    <div class="law-box">
      <div class="law-title">7. Phishing and Online Fraud</div>
      <div class="law-section"><span class="label">Definition:</span> Deceiving users into giving up sensitive information online.</div>
      <div class="law-section"><span class="label">Example:</span> In 2020, users received fake emails appearing to be from banks asking for OTPs, resulting in stolen funds.</div>
      <div class="law-section"><span class="label">Crime Under:</span> IT Act Section 66D</div>
    </div>

  </div>

